        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> I believe there is an issue with the build. After the first build (maven clean install), the Grizzly server gave me a not found for the root context, after running the org.onap.policy.gui.editors.apex.rest.ApexEditorMain class. On the second build though, it worked.\n> I've tried also in a clean repo folder, and got the same behavior.\n> Not sure what is happening.\n\nTested here three times and on the last one the problem did not happen. Maybe, it was local problem, not sure, as in previous versions I've not seen this.\n\nAnother thing I got was the \"double\" generation of dist folder files in the gui-editors/gui-editor-apex/target/classes/webapp folder. The root and /dist folders contains duplicated content. Probably you don't want to include the dist folder there. Neither build configuration files like /package.json, /package-lock.json, /webpack.config.js, /.babelrc.",
        "patchset_number": 2
